issues.fix:
Replace static variable with a global variable or use WordPress transients/options to track if modal has been rendered. Example:

Before lines 112-115:
if ( ! isset( $GLOBALS['takt_testimonial_modal_rendered'] ) ) {
	$GLOBALS['takt_testimonial_modal_rendered'] = true;

This ensures the flag persists across all block renders in the same request.

Add explicit focus styles to .modal-close-btn class:

.modal-close-btn:focus-visible {
	@apply ring-2 ring-white ring-offset-2 ring-offset-black/80;
}

Or use outline:

.modal-close-btn:focus-visible {
	outline: 2px solid white;
	outline-offset: 4px;
}
